'''Reverb''' is a [[non-profit]] [[Environmentalism|environmental]] organization that educates and engages musicians and their fans to promote environmental [[sustainability]]. It was founded by environmentalist Lauren Sullivan and her musician husband, [[Guster]] guitarist/vocalist [[Adam Gardner]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.marketwire.com/press-release/jason-mraz-teams-up-with-britar-filterforgoodr-music-project-reduce-bottled-water-waste-1691295.htm | title=Jason Mraz Teams Up With Brita® FilterForGood® Music Project to Reduce Bottled Water Waste on North American Tour | publisher=http://www.marketwire.com/ | date=August 15, 2012 | accessdate=September 26, 2012 | author=Kargas, David}}</ref>

Reverb's greening services include [[carbon neutral]] concerts and venues; [[biodiesel]] for vehicles and generators; [[waste reduction]]; [[biodegradable]] catering products; [[recycling]]; green bus supplies and cleaners; [[Efficient energy use|energy efficiency]]; green contract rider; eco-friendly merchandise; green sponsorship; and on site and on-line fan outreach.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.greenandsave.com/green_news/green_entertainment/rocking_to_a_new_tune_reverb_helps_greenup_2009_summer_concert_tours | title=Rocking to a New Tune – Reverb Helps Green-Up 2009 Summer Concert Tours | publisher=www.greenandsave.com/ | date=26th April 2009 | accessdate=September 26, 2012 | author=Rice, Shawn}}</ref>

Reverb's "Eco-Village" provides fans with a "hands on" learning experience that engages them with local non-profit groups, and gives them the opportunity to volunteer with tree, and environment-focused groups within their community. Fans can also donate money for the cause and receive a souvenir sticker.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.marketwire.com/press-release/jason-mraz-teams-up-with-britar-filterforgoodr-music-project-reduce-bottled-water-waste-1691295.htm | title=Jason Mraz Teams Up With Brita® FilterForGood® Music Project to Reduce Bottled Water Waste on North American Tour | publisher=http://www.marketwire.com/ | date=August 15, 2012 | accessdate=September 26, 2012 | author=Kargas, David}}</ref>

Reverb has worked with such artists as [[Alanis Morissette]], [[Avril Lavigne]], [[Barenaked Ladies]], [[Beastie Boys]], [[Blue Man Group]], [[Bonnie Raitt]], [[Brandi Carlile]], [[Dave Matthews Band]], [[Fall Out Boy]] and the [[Honda Civic Tour]], [[Jack Johnson (musician)|Jack Johnson]], [[John Mayer]], [[Norah Jones]], [[Red Hot Chili Peppers]], [[Sheryl Crow]], [[The String Cheese Incident]], [[The Fray]], [[Phish]], [[Jason Mraz]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.marketwire.com/press-release/jason-mraz-teams-up-with-britar-filterforgoodr-music-project-reduce-bottled-water-waste-1691295.htm | title=Jason Mraz Teams Up With Brita® FilterForGood® Music Project to Reduce Bottled Water Waste on North American Tour | publisher=http://www.marketwire.com/ | date=August 15, 2012 | accessdate=September 26, 2012 | author=Kargas, David}}</ref>, and others.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.greenandsave.com/green_news/green_entertainment/rocking_to_a_new_tune_reverb_helps_greenup_2009_summer_concert_tours | title=Rocking to a New Tune – Reverb Helps Green-Up 2009 Summer Concert Tours | publisher=www.greenandsave.com/ | date=26th April 2009 | accessdate=September 26, 2012 | author=Rice, Shawn}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.paenvironmentdigest.com/newsletter/default.asp?NewsletterArticleID=8589&SubjectID= | title=Spotlight - Guster Is First Artist Featured on PA Environmental Council’s New Website | publisher=http://www.paenvironmentdigest.com | date=2/1/2008 | accessdate=September 26, 2012}}</ref>

